<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263436>
    dc:description "PLATE 136. Neodrillia cydia Bartsch, 1943. Upper panel. Figs. 1 – 2: holotype, off Fowey Light, Miami-Dade Co., E Florida (USNM 411099). Fig. 1: ventral, lateral & dorsal views; Fig. 2: apical view, V = varix, L = edge of lower lip. Figs 3 – 6: synonyms of N. cydia. Fig. 3: Neodrillia jamaicensis Bartsch, 1943, holotype, Jamaica (USNM 103394); Fig. 4: Neodrillia encia Bartsch, 1943, holotype, St Thomas (USNM 214261); Fig. 5: Neodrillia antiguensis Bartsch 1943, holotype, Falmouth, Antigua (USNM 516298); Fig. 6: Neodrillia barbadensis Bartsch, 1943, holotype, Barbados (USNM 516302). Lower panel. Figs. 7 – 9: off Jacksonville, Duval Co., E Florida (EFG 10070); Fig. 10: NW of Loggerhead Key, Dry Tortugas, FL Keys (EFG 25503); Figs. 11 – 12: Ewing Bank, Louisiana (EFG 23437); Fig. 13: off SW Curacao, off Gulf Co., W Florida (DMNH 114864); Fig. 14: W of Hernando Co., W Florida (EFG 27547); Figs. 15 – 16: W of Egmont Key, Hillsborough Co., W Florida (EFG 12984); Fig. 17: off Anna Maria I., Manatee Co., W Florida (DMNH 114833); Fig. 18: W of Boca Grande, Charlotte Co., W Florida (EFG 11556); Figs. 19 – 20: Eleuthera I., Bahama Is. (author’s coll.); Fig. 21: Cat Cay, Bimini Is., Bahama Is. (author’s coll.); Fig. 22: Dog Rocks, Cay Sal Bank, Bahama Is. (author’s coll.)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263436/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263437>
    dc:description "PLATE 137. Neodrillia cydia Bartsch, 1943. Specimens from the Greater and Lesser Antilles, W Caribbean, and northern South America. Figs. 1, 7: Maria La Gorda, Pinar del Rio Prov., Cuba (author’s coll.); Figs. 2 – 3: south coast, Cuba (author’s coll.); Figs. 4 – 6: W of Punta Aguila, Puerto Rico (author’s coll.); Figs. 8 – 9: Little St. James I., St. Thomas, U. S. V. I. (author’s coll.); Figs. 10 – 11: Inodrillia ustickei Hayes, 1959, N of Frederiksted, St. Croix, U. S. V. I.: Fig. 10: lectotype (AMNH 195463); Fig. 11: paralectotype (UF 156156); Fig. 12: Ilet Cochon, Guadeloupe (MNHN IM- 2013 - 20153); Fig. 13: Les 3 arches (Port- Louis), Guadeloupe (MNHN IM- 2013 - 7781); Fig. 14: Anse d'Arlet, Martinique (MNHN ex R. Delannoye coll.); Fig. 15: St. Martin (MNHM ex J. Colomb coll.); Fig. 16: N Point, Chatham Bay, Union I., SVG (author’s coll.); Fig. 17: S side of Norde de Ouest, Mayreau I., SVG (author’s coll.); Fig. 18: Anse Chemin, Bequia I., SVG (author’s coll.); Figs. 19 – 20: Large I., Grenada (author’s coll.); Fig. 21: Mt. Irving Bay, Tobago I. Trinidad & Tobago (author’s coll.); Fig. 22: WNW of Jeremi Beach, Curaçao, Neth. Antilles (author’s coll.); Fig. 23: Punta Braboe, Aruba, Neth. Antilles (author’s coll.); Fig. 24: off Punta San Blas, San Blas Is., Panama (author’s coll.); Fig. 25: Tayrona National Park, Magdalena Dept., Colombia (author’s coll.); Fig. 26: Coledup, San Blas Is., Panama (author’s coll.); Fig. 27: Utila I., Honduras (author’s coll.); Fig. 28: Vivorillo Cays, Bay Is., Honduras (author’s coll.); Fig. 29: Dixon Cove, Roatan I., Bay Is., Honduras (author’s coll.); Fig. 30: Chinchorro Bank, Quintana Roo, Mexico (author’s coll.)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263437/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

